    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-07-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-07-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="386"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d386">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.00/878.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 323.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-07-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 2, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: While there have been no radical developments
                    since Estenoz was killed, I think I may safely say that the situation has
                    improved to a remarked degree, and that a very encouraging change is manifest in
                    public confidence. It is, of course, impossible to predict with certainty what
                    may happen so long as Ivonet and other leaders contrive to elude capture, but it
                    is now generally believed that the Government has the upper hand and will, with
                    a proper display of energy, be able completely to crush the revolt.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">A. M. Beaupré</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
